### Test API Endpoints
### Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code to use these

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = 

### 1. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Login - Get Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jean@kfh.rw",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get Hospitals
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/hospitals

### 4. Get Referrals (requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/referrals
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get Patients (requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/patients
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Get Referral Statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/referrals/stats
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Create Patient
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/patients
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "gender": "male",
  "dob": "1990-01-15",
  "phone": "0780000000",
  "address": "Kigali, Rwanda",
  "nationalId": "1199999999999999"
}

### 8. Create Referral
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/referrals
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientId": "pat-01",
  "reason": "Heart condition check",
  "priority": "Routine",
  "receivingHospitalId": "hosp-02",
  "department": "Cardiology"
}

### 9. Update Referral Status
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/referrals/ref-1001/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "approved"
}

### 10. Get Audit Logs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/audit
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Get All Users (admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 12. Verify Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
### INSTRUCTIONS:
### 1. Run "Login - Get Token" endpoint first
### 2. Copy the token from response
### 3. Update @token variable at top with the token value
### 4. Now all protected endpoints will work
### 5. Click "Send Request" above each endpoint to test
